These citizens will be coming out into our communities so it’s important that we prepare them to re-enter society free of those issues that may have contributed to their problem. Our program is heavily invested in Mentors on the outside who volunteer to be trained as Mentors to those who are incarcerated from the convenience of their home through emails and video chats. There is no in-prison mentoring is required, unless you choose to go in with our teams. The Christian program uses a 4 Phase “I See ME Free” Curriculum Manuals developed by Pamela (Winderweedle) Hillman, each over 200-pages that cover the 12-month committed mentoring period. Description: Nautical Monkey is a social networking platform connecting boaters with potential partners to help reduce their costs.
Full Description: Nautical Monkey is a social networking platform connecting boaters with potential partners to help reduce their costs. There are more than 70 million Americans enjoying boating  and approximately 17 million registered recreational vessels in the United States , however on average a boat is only used a total of 14 days per year. Boat owners are looking for a way to maximize their investment but are hesitant to look for a partner do to the inherent challenges that come with sharing a boat. Nautical Monkey is an online service and management tool that takes users through each stage of the process. The online calendar will provide instant access to all activities and reservations, notification of cancellations and changes (via email or text message), as well detailed information about local events.    Members can instantly update trip information such as engine hours and fuel usage via the mobile site as well as submit maintenance and service requests (even if they are still out on the boat).   The online service log allows users to record regular maintenance for easy reference and even notifies you when maintenance is overdue.  Finally, automated billing allows users forget the business of boat ownership and enjoy  the benefits.

Description: Moving Image Source is a website dedicated to the history of film, television, and digital media.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Moving Image Source is a website dedicated to the history of film, television, and digital media. It features original articles by primary critics, authors, and scholars; a calendar that highlights major retrospectives, festivals, and gallery exhibitions at venues around the world; and a regularly updated guide to online research resources. Moving Image Source is updated regularly with additions to the articles and calendar sections. The articles relate to recent and ongoing retrospectives and gallery exhibitions as well as to significant new DVDs and books on film, media, and moving-image culture. Its calendar is a selective guide to major screenings, series, festivals, and gallery exhibitions that also include program summaries, exhibition descriptions, titles of films or featured works of media art, and links to the presenting venues. Moving Image Source’s calendar draws on the programming of more than 100 museums, media arts centers, cinematheques, and other venues that regularly present film and media programs. An international venue list can also be found in its calendar section and the venues on the list emphasize original programming and the presentation of work in its original format or large-scale gallery exhibitions. The Moving Image Source’s research guide is an annotated and regularly maintained database of more than 400 of the best moving-image related resources on the web, ranging from scholarly and popular journals to film-related libraries and archives. It is based in New York, N.Y.

Description: Boardwalk Bites is a family-owned carnival food truck. It is popular in Allen, Texas for their funnel cakes, corn dogs, and lemonades.
Full Description: We are happy to say that we are the best Carnival Food Truck in Texas. Our family is passionate about food, and we all have different taste preferences. To relive the nostalgia of our childhood memories, we chose to highlight state fair treats. Our shared love for food and its ability to bring people together inspired us to embark on our first food venture. We began with a humble tent that offered freshly hand-popped kettle corn, which became a hit. Encouraged by our success, we expanded our menu and invested in our first food truck, Zaza, to bring our treats on the road. Over the years, we have served at various large fairs, festivals, school events, churches, weddings, corporate lunches, graduation parties, and birthdays. After five years of being mobile, we decided to expand our business further. We purchased a second food truck, Ziggy, which continues to travel to events. Meanwhile, Zaza is stationed at the Allen Premium Outlet Mall, providing walk-up service to our community all year round.

Through these experiences, along with cultivating business relationships in the energy community, they quickly realized that no comprehensive data reporting solution existed in the commodity markets. They believe their product fills this untapped space and will benefit organizations, agnostic of industry, that deal with managing multiple systems or processes, operational tracking, and accounting reconciliations test. Utilizing their expertise in the commodity trading and risk management market, Connective Reporting solutions is developing a one-of-a-kind data lifecycle intelligence platform. Designed to bridge disparate data and provide enhanced visibility and insights, their solution will give companies a deeper understanding of the organizational information they rely upon when making important business decisions. Their cloud-based, scalable solution will be priced competitively when compared to custom-build alternatives currently available in the market. The product(s) will provide configuration flexibility, allowing a client to customize the software to fit their needs while maintaining the core functionality of their product. Their ability to manage and be agnostic to sources creates a unique advantage in being able to deliver timely information back to the business.

Description: Hodyon is a manufacturer and distributor of energy-efficient products and systems.
Full Description: Hodyon is a manufacturer and distributor of energy-efficient products and systems that reduce the magnitude of climate change. The company is ISO 9001:2000 certified and the 59th fastest growing, privately-held manufacturer in the U.S., according to Inc. Magazine.   Located in Round Rock (greater Austin), Texas, with 28 employees,  Auxiliary power units (APUs) are used on heavy trucks to provide power for heating and air conditioning, lighting and electronic systems in circumstances where the diesel engine must be turned off.  Hodyon's diesel-electric Dynasys™ APU system provides dependable comfort for the driver during down times, reduces emissions and lowers fuel costs during stops (vs. idling of the main engine).  Hodyon's current APU embodies a design it considers superior and the company provides field support, customer service and product fleet trial programs viewed by customers as significantly better than the competition.
